	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
			<p rend="indent(8)"><placeName>Montreal</placeName> <date>6 Jany 53</date></p>
				<p>Dear Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Your favor of the <date>11th dec</date> came in due<lb/> course with <date>Dec</date> Occidents its too early to look for<lb/> the <date>Jany</date> No&#39;s   I enclose herein the Amount<lb/> of <persName>Mr. G. Benjamin&#39;s</persName> dues which I have&#44; at length<lb/> succeeded in obtaining&#8212;as yet all I have been<lb/> able to collect.   You do not seem to be aware<lb/> that <persName>Mr Desola</persName> is republishing his Prayer books in<lb/> <placeName>London</placeName>. At least the volume is printed.  I have not<lb/> heard the price. But as nearly all the members of<lb/> this congregation visit <placeName>England</placeName> very frequently<lb/> they will be apt to provide themselves with setts<lb/> there. Which they are enabled to bring out without<lb/> any expense.  I also notice some cheap editions<lb/> of the Bible advertised in the Chronicle.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Your a&#47;ct was sent to <persName>Mr Levy</persName> who informs<lb/> me that he paid for the Books&#95;but that he would<lb/> transmit the Bill to <persName>Mr Lyons</persName>&#8212;you must hear in<lb/> mind that having admitted that you had claimed<lb/> from <persName>Mr Lyons</persName> entirely relieves <persName>Mr Levy</persName> from any<lb/> objection to pay again for the Books.  He leaves<lb/> tomorrow for <placeName>Europe</placeName>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Dr. David</persName> held in intercourse with the Editor<lb/> of the Asmoneon.  His work was sent&#44; I believe&#44;<lb/> after the lapse of some time to numerous Editors</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>in the <placeName>United States</placeName> and heard it preached<lb/> that of two Jewish publications&#45;notice was taken<lb/> of it in one only.  As you profess to record events<lb/> connected with our people it was thought singular<lb/> that the only work published in <placeName>Canada</placeName> of the<lb/> kind would have been considered beneath<lb/> your notice.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Winter has but just commenced &#38; the <placeName>St Lawrence</placeName><lb/> was yesterday frozen over. Within a week we have<lb/> had enough snow for a season.  You would be<lb/> better off here than at <placeName>St. Louis</placeName> &#40;as we have only<lb/> to cross the River to reach Railroads to all<lb/> parts of the <placeName>United States</placeName>.  You did not<lb/> state the cost of some books you forwarded for the<lb/> Sunday School please let me know that I may send<lb/> you the Amount.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I enclose thirty Dollars say pee<add>&#63;</add> of Order for <date>1851</date> &#38; <date>1852</date>. 1.10.0<lb/> <persName>G Benjamin</persName> <date>1846</date>.<date>1847</date>.<date>1848</date>.<date>1849</date>.<date>1850</date>.<date>1851</date> &#38; <date>1852</date> &#61; 7 years</p>
				<p><add>&#63;</add>&#58; c15&#47; &#38; publications 18&#47;9&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;5.18.9</p>
				<p><persName>Kahen</persName>&#47;<placeName>Toronto</placeName> paid in full for 6 mo&#39;s having left the<lb/> province 5 <add>&#63;</add> subscriber since <date>Oct</date>&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;0.7.6</p>
				<p>or &#36;31.75 leaving &#36;1&#47;4 to be accounted for&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;7.16.3</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Please acknowledge rect of subscriptions from <persName>Goodman<lb/> Benjamin&#39;s</persName> <add>&#63;</add> in our next Occident<lb/> <persName>Mr <add>&#63;</add></persName><lb/> &#38;Remain yr Srvt</p>
				<p><persName role="author">J. S. Joseph</persName></p>
		</body>
